FBIS3-23407 "jptot013__l94088" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 24 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA LEBANON Suspects in June 1993 Bombing Get Death Sentences Six Get Death Sentence NC2403144794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1400 GMT 24 Mar 94 NC2403144794 Beirut Radio Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Examining Magistrate Fawzi Daghir, who is investigating the bombing of Sayyidat Dayr al-Balamand, today passed the death sentence against the six detained criminals. He dropped charges against defendant 'Abdallah al-Hilu, who is now dead. Judge Daghir instructed the security service to arrest the real motivators. He dropped charges against two defendants because of a lack of evidence. Judge Sa'id Mirza demanded that the death sentence be passed against 16 people -- three detained and 13 fugitive -- on charges of killing Jordanian diplomat Na'ib al-Ma'ayitah in January.
